The paper deals with automatic extraction of relations from semi-structured websites, which involves techniques from information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) for analyzing web pages and extracting structured information. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely categories. The paper also involves machine learning techniques for training classifiers to predict relation instances, which falls under the categories of cs.AI and cs.LG. Finally, the paper deals with the use of knowledge bases and databases for generating training labels and storing extracted information, which falls under the category of cs.DB.
